subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis. Medium-sized to large, length: 3.2 –5.0 mm, entirely black-bronze or bronze, exceptionally blue; frons shallowly grooved, with rather long, white pubescence; antennae short, barely reaching midlength of lateral pronotal margins; pronotal margins broadly curved, lateroposterior depressions wide, shallow, pronotal disc exceptionally with two small, round impressions; elytra subparallel, 1.35–1.40 times as long as wide, obliquely angled to the rounded apices; maximum elytral length at suture; aedeagus elongate, flattened, parameres broadened basal to the midlength without preapical spines (
Fig. 66
).
